  "text": "One way of implementing hiding in the time dimension in software implementations is by using a random shuffling method. This method seeks to randomly change the sequence in which the operations of an algorithm are performed. In AES, for example, the order in which the S-Box look up is carried out on each of the 16 bytes of the state does not affect the state of the algorithm at the end of SubBytes. This kind of shuffling can be done either by selecting a random start index for loops or by permuting the state bytes of the algorithm before entering the loop [CITATION_1] .",
